WHEREAS, the Veterans Heritage Site Foundation is hosting a Women Veterans
Appreciation Day program on June 12, 2025, and has also established a Women Veterans
Appreciation Week, June 8-14, 2025, in tribute to our gallant women veterans; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we are proud to join with the
Veterans Heritage Site Foundation in the commemoration of June 12, 2025, as "Women
Veterans Appreciation Day" in Tennessee to honor the growing presence of women in all
branches of United States Armed Forces and their valiant service and sacrifices on behalf of the
State of Tennessee and the United States of America.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
